      },
      "date": "2013-02-14 15:43:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\n(6 inline comments)\n\n",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
    {
      "id": "aae0c5946127fb6b9f72d59418e7ad5027b50b32",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 119,
        "name": "Alex Zhuravlev",
        "email": "bzzz@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "bzzz"
      },
      "date": "2013-02-14 15:49:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 7:\n\nanother approach could be to get back to old (normal) lock-transaction order, which would improve other cases as well (like setstripe vs. unlink race, lfsck).\n\ni believe the only reason to lock the parent in mdd_create() is to maintain i_nlink consistent, but this is already done by osd means, internally. once we don't need to lock the parent (so no problems with pdirops) we can start to grab lock on a child before transaction.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 7
    },
